[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     939[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     940[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The pipeline keeps a live state object per patient on DynamoDB. The state holds the recent samples per parameter (a bounded deque so the memory does not grow), the current rolling baseline per parameter (computed from clean, non-suspicious samples over the baseline window), the current alert state (idle / watch / concern / rapid-response), and the last-paged timestamp per tier. Production runs this as a Flink keyed-stream operator with the patient identifier as the key, which gives O(1) per-record access to the state and lets the operator persist incrementally to DynamoDB in the background. The demo runs the same logic synchronously against a `MockTable`.
