[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The hardest part of the pipeline is not detecting deterioration. It is deciding whether the detected deterioration is worth a page. Step 5 layers persistence checks, deduplication against the patient's existing alert state, and a tier-specific refractory window so the same deterioration does not produce ten pages in five minutes. Alerts that survive get a row in the alert ledger on DynamoDB, a page on the appropriate SNS topic, and a lifecycle event on EventBridge. Suppressed alerts get logged to S3 so the calibration team can tune the rules week over week.
