[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion implements the full Recipe 12.7 pattern end-to-end across all five pseudocode steps (ingest/validate/normalize, artifact filter, per-patient state and rolling baseline, composite score and trajectory slope detection, suppression and delivery). boto3 usage is correct: clients for kinesis, s3, events, cloudwatch, sns, sagemaker-runtime, and lambda are constructed with a sensible adaptive-retry Config, and a dynamodb resource is used; mock classes mirror real API shapes (put_record, put_object/get_object, put_item/get_item/update_item/query, put_events, publish, put_metric_data) so the production swap is direct. Error-handling commentary is thorough: dead-letter prefix on validation failure, unsupported unit conversion, device-quality artifact handling, BatchWriteItem UnprocessedItems guidance, retry/throttling notes, refractory and persistence gates, suppressed-alert logging, and structured-logging/PHI cautions are all explicitly addressed. The detectors (ArtifactDetector, EarlyWarningScorer, TrajectorySlopeDetector) are functional implementations with real math (interquartile mean, MAD, linear regression, NEWS2-shaped bands) rather than stubs, [3mto[23mdecimal handles DynamoDB float restrictions, and run_demo wires the synthetic stream through process_record to produce surfaced/suppressed/artifact outcomes. No NotImplementedError, no pass-only function bodies, and no placeholder code paths; the only TODOs are markdown cross-references to sibling recipes, not code stubs."}